&lt;p&gt;Al Aqsa Mosque in occupied East Jerusalem reopened on Thursday after being closed for 40 days by Israel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The mosque, located in the Old City, was reopened at dawn, allowing hundreds of Palestinian Muslims to enter the Al-Haram al-Sharif compound.&lt;/p&gt;
